<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12004e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12004e">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12004e"> 4(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> curse of baldness</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Un jour, un m&eacute;cr&eacute;ant voulut lui donner un coup de b&ecirc;che. Pour le punir, le saint lui proph&eacute;tisa que sa post&eacute;rit&eacute;, jusqu&apos;&agrave; la vingti&egrave;me g&eacute;n&eacute;ration, <mark>serait chauve</mark>. Et il para&icirc;t que depuis lors, dans la famille de cet anticl&eacute;rical avant la lettre, hommes et femmes sont afflig&eacute;s d&apos;une calvitie compl&egrave;te et incurable. <br><font color="green">[One day, a miscreant wanted to hit him with a spade. To punish him, the saint prophesied that for twenty generations all his descendants <mark>would be bald</mark>. And it came to pass since then that in the family of this anti-cleric <i>avant la lettre</i>, all the men and the women were afflicted with complete and incurable baldness.]</font> <small> l'Abb&eacute; A. Millon, <a name="AMPB" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#AMPB"><cite title="source">Pauvres Pierres! Les Megalithes Bretons devant la science</cite></a> (n.d) 9</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
